theorem closure_union_interior_complement {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    (A : Set X) :
    closure (A : Set X) ∪ interior ((Aᶜ) : Set X) = (Set.univ : Set X) := by
  classical
  -- We prove the equality by showing mutual inclusion.
  apply Set.Subset.antisymm
  · -- Left-to-right inclusion is immediate.
    intro x _
    exact Set.mem_univ _
  · -- For the converse inclusion, fix any `x : X`.
    intro x _
    by_cases hxCl : (x : X) ∈ closure (A : Set X)
    · -- The easy case `x ∈ closure A`.
      exact Or.inl hxCl
    · -- Otherwise, `x ∉ closure A`.
      have hxNotCl : (x : X) ∈ ((closure (A : Set X))ᶜ : Set X) := hxCl
      -- The complement of `closure A` is open …
      have hOpen :
          IsOpen ((closure (A : Set X))ᶜ : Set X) :=
        (isClosed_closure : IsClosed (closure (A : Set X))).isOpen_compl
      -- … and contained in `Aᶜ`.
      have hSub :
          ((closure (A : Set X))ᶜ : Set X) ⊆ (Aᶜ : Set X) := by
        intro y hyNotCl
        by_contra hyA
        have : (y : X) ∈ closure (A : Set X) := subset_closure hyA
        exact hyNotCl this
      -- Hence, every point of the open set belongs to `interior (Aᶜ)`.
      have hInside :
          ((closure (A : Set X))ᶜ : Set X) ⊆ interior ((Aᶜ) : Set X) :=
        interior_maximal hSub hOpen
      -- In particular, this holds for our point `x`.
      have hxIntComp : (x : X) ∈ interior ((Aᶜ) : Set X) :=
        hInside hxNotCl
      exact Or.inr hxIntComp
